name: Sea Shells by James

reviews.review_text: As it was 11 they switched off the light on the deck. Had to eat in the dark. The food service was quick and the food was very good. But had to blindly eat as the lights were switched off and they could not put it back as it was 11.  Must try BBQ chicken wings, stuffed mushrooms and chicken fried rice. And beware about water bottles. They made us buy it even though we did not order nor use it.

I had a very bad experience the first time I visited. Just coz the restaurant was full the waiters did not bother to acknowledge us. We were also given a table which was positioned in the hot sun and when asked to move a bit they refused. But each place deserves a second chance. So the next time I went (was after a year).

The sea view is great. The ambiance is amazing. A very chill place to hang out but the food was okayish. Not soo great or good I’d rather say for the price point. Soo not very happy with it. 3 stars only for the ambiance.

The portions have become smaller but the flavours more than compensate for it.
Excellent vibe, great view , prompt service and fantastic new decor.  The day we went there was live music by Sherwyn... he was outstanding!!!
We love this place as a family and have been frequenting it ..
Keep going!

description:
### Sea Shells by James: A Coastal Gem in Bambolim

Nestled along the serene shores of Bambolim Camp, **Sea Shells by James** has garnered an impressive *4.1 rating from 4,658 reviews*, making it a noteworthy spot for both locals and tourists. Renowned for its **Goan food**, the restaurant captures the essence of coastal dining with an enchanting ambiance perfect for enjoying sunsets (remarked upon by 39 patrons), live music, and a relaxed atmosphere.

#### Ambiance & Design

As you approach Sea Shells, the striking decor draws you in—modern yet approachable, with a blend of nautical themes and comfortable seating arrangements. The restaurant features an evocative deck area where the best views of the shore can be enjoyed, albeit with some reviews mentioning that the lighting is turned off promptly at 11 PM, leading to a few awkward dining experiences in the dark. One photo vividly captures the **breathtaking sea view**, perfect for unwinding during golden hour, while the lively ambiance with patrons enjoying **live performances by bands** like Sherwyn infuses energy into the space.

A few guests have highlighted the fantastic vibes, especially on evenings filled with music, enhancing the dining experience amidst the gentle sound of waves lapping against the shore. While the decor has received praise for being vibrant and inviting (as seen in our third image link), it's crucial to note that seating arrangements can sometimes hinder comfort, especially during peak hours.

#### Menu & Culinary Experience

The culinary offerings at Sea Shells are diverse, with **signature dishes** like BBQ chicken wings, stuffed mushrooms, and chicken fried rice stealing the spotlight as must-tries, as noted by several guests. Though some customers have expressed dissatisfaction with portion sizes, stating they have "become smaller," many agree that the flavors more than make up for it. Intriguingly, the balance between flavor richness and portion sizes has led to varying experiences across multiple visits.

In terms of dietary options, the menu appears to cater well to a broad audience; however, ensuring customer satisfaction seems paramount, as reflected in feedback about pricing relative to food quality. The presentation of dishes showcased in customer photographs reflects a commitment to aesthetics, with vibrant dishes that echo the colorful culture of Goa.

#### Customer Experience & Service

Customer service at Sea Shells has drawn mixed reviews. While many commend the **quick food service** and prompt staff, instances of slower attention during busier times have also been documented. Patrons appreciated the efficiency shown in the execution of orders, although frustrations arise when requests to change tables or other accommodations are unmet—the latter especially noted by a returning customer who highlighted the need for acknowledgment from staff during busy times.

It's suggested for prospective visitors to manage expectations regarding peak hours and consider making reservations, as footfall can swell rapidly, particularly for the prime sunset view tables.

#### Popularity & Reviews

The buzz around Sea Shells extends beyond the reviews, with numerous patrons sharing their experiences on social media platforms, praising its vibrant ambiance and live entertainment. Notably, despite varied experiences, many customers reiterate their desire to return, showcasing the restaurant's resilient charm.  

In conclusion, Sea Shells by James stands as a beautiful, albeit occasionally inconsistent, dining venue on the stunning Bambolim shore. With a solid base of shared experiences, its reputation remains buoyed by a blend of great food, live music, and breathtaking views, ensuring it remains at the top of the must-visit list for those craving an authentic taste of Goan cuisine.
